                            <comment id="15018194" author="stephanewen" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 15:56:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;will be API breaking, though...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15024130" author="aljoscha" created="Tue, 24 Nov 2015 09:54:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What do we gain by removing the return type? I agree that we should synchronize it between &lt;tt&gt;Ser&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;Deser&lt;/tt&gt; schema, though.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15024145" author="stephanewen" created="Tue, 24 Nov 2015 09:58:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think that was Robert&apos;s intention. The SerSchema should always create a byte[].&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15024155" author="rmetzger" created="Tue, 24 Nov 2015 10:02:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is some nonsensical stuff going on with the Kafka serializers.&lt;br/&gt;
The &lt;tt&gt;SimpleStringSchema&lt;/tt&gt;&apos;s &lt;tt&gt;serialize()&lt;/tt&gt; method is just wrong, so you can only use the schema for deserializing. For serializing, you have to use the &lt;tt&gt;JavaDefaultStringSchema&lt;/tt&gt;. (This one is doing the ser and deser correctly, but using the commons lang &lt;tt&gt;SerializationUtils&lt;/tt&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With a stricter &lt;tt&gt;SerializationSchema&lt;/tt&gt;, the &lt;tt&gt;SimpleStringSchema&lt;/tt&gt; wouldn&apos;t be wrong.  Currently, all instances of the &lt;tt&gt;SerializationSchema&lt;/tt&gt; are using &lt;tt&gt;byte[]&lt;/tt&gt; returns.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15026969" author="githubbot" created="Wed, 25 Nov 2015 15:53:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user rmetzger opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/1406&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/1406&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-3054&quot; title=&quot;Remove R (return) type variable from SerializationSchema&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-3054&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-3054&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Remove R (return) type variable from SerializationSchema&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;I removed the `JavaDefaultStringSchema`, `DummyStringSchema`, `StringToByteSerializer` and used the `SimpleStringSchema` everywhere.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;I removed the `RawSchema`, it was not used anywhere.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


